&lt;p&gt;The Product Management team at Weight Watchers is rebuilding the digital product portfolio of a trusted 60-year-old brand, applying the latest in nutrition science, behavioral science, AI, and clinical care. Our mission is to improve the health and longevity of our members by building the best holistic weight health platform in the market. We operate at a significant scale and continue to invest in the velocity of our product execution.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will own the tactical execution of our acquisition testing program from hypothesis to live experiment to post-experiment readout across landing pages, the Med+ quiz, plans, checkout, and promotional configuration. The role is responsible for the throughput of the Growth team&#39;s experimentation roadmap and works closely with Marketing, Design, and Engineering to take new tests from idea to in-market in days, not weeks.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Own the Experimentation Roadmap: &lt;/strong&gt;Work with Principal PM to identify strategic opportunities for experiments.&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;Maintain a prioritized, continuously-running testing roadmap across various landing pages and sign-up funnels.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Operationalize Test Velocity: &lt;/strong&gt;Partner with Marketing, Design, and Engineering to take hypotheses from idea to live test within a sprint. Own the documentation, configuration, and analytics setup that make high-volume testing sustainable.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Optimize the Med+ Funnel: &lt;/strong&gt;Identify drop-off points across the Med+ acquisition flow (LP, quiz, plans, payment) and maintain a backlog of the highest-leverage fixes and experiments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Surface Insights from Data: &lt;/strong&gt;Translate results from product launches into clear, actionable recommendations for the Marketing team and senior leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Drive Cross-Functional Velocity: &lt;/strong&gt;Work with stakeholders in Marketing, Compliance, and Design to focus on driving strategic initiatives forward.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who You Are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Analytical and detail-oriented: &lt;/strong&gt;Comfortable in spreadsheets, product analytics platforms, and experiment design.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Velocity-minded: &lt;/strong&gt;Prioritize speed of learning over perfect execution; pragmatic about trade-offs that accelerate the testing cycle.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cross-functional collaborator: &lt;/strong&gt;Operate effectively at the intersection of Marketing, Design, and Engineering, and translate clearly between business problem and technical execution.&lt;/li&gt;
